      @contract  executes the named module file as a fresh chunk, passing `deps` as its `...` argument. Used for factory modules whose file body IS the constructor (vs. stateless `require`d tables). Test seam: a function in util._stubs[name] takes precedence and is called with deps — so harnesses can swap a fake without altering the production graph.  @ 639

